#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:8
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:10
msgid ""
"dm-clone is a device mapper target which produces a one-to-one copy of an "
"existing, read-only source device into a writable destination device: It "
"presents a virtual block device which makes all data appear immediately, and "
"redirects reads and writes accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:15
msgid ""
"The main use case of dm-clone is to clone a potentially remote, high-"
"latency, read-only, archival-type block device into a writable, fast, "
"primary-type device for fast, low-latency I/O. The cloned device is visible/"
"mountable immediately and the copy of the source device to the destination "
"device happens in the background, in parallel with user I/O."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:21
msgid ""
"For example, one could restore an application backup from a read-only copy, "
"accessible through a network storage protocol (NBD, Fibre Channel, iSCSI, "
"AoE, etc.), into a local SSD or NVMe device, and start using the device "
"immediately, without waiting for the restore to complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:26
msgid ""
"When the cloning completes, the dm-clone table can be removed altogether and "
"be replaced, e.g., by a linear table, mapping directly to the destination "
"device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:29
msgid ""
"The dm-clone target reuses the metadata library used by the thin-"
"provisioning target."
msgstr ""

