#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:49
msgid ""
"The target is constructed by passing three devices to it (along with other "
"parameters detailed later):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:52
msgid ""
"A source device - the read-only device that gets cloned and source of the "
"hydration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:55
msgid ""
"A destination device - the destination of the hydration, which will become a "
"clone of the source device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:58
msgid ""
"A small metadata device - it records which regions are already valid in the "
"destination device, i.e., which regions have already been hydrated, or have "
"been written to directly, via user I/O."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:62
msgid ""
"The size of the destination device must be at least equal to the size of the "
"source device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:66
msgid "Regions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:68
msgid ""
"dm-clone divides the source and destination devices in fixed sized regions. "
"Regions are the unit of hydration, i.e., the minimum amount of data copied "
"from the source to the destination device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:72
msgid ""
"The region size is configurable when you first create the dm-clone device. "
"The recommended region size is the same as the file system block size, which "
"usually is 4KB. The region size must be between 8 sectors (4KB) and 2097152 "
"sectors (1GB) and a power of two."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:77
msgid ""
"Reads and writes from/to hydrated regions are serviced from the destination "
"device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:80
msgid ""
"A read to a not yet hydrated region is serviced directly from the source "
"device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:82
msgid ""
"A write to a not yet hydrated region will be delayed until the corresponding "
"region has been hydrated and the hydration of the region starts immediately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:85
msgid ""
"Note that a write request with size equal to region size will skip copying "
"of the corresponding region from the source device and overwrite the region "
"of the destination device directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:90
msgid "Discards"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:92
msgid ""
"dm-clone interprets a discard request to a range that hasn't been hydrated "
"yet as a hint to skip hydration of the regions covered by the request, i.e., "
"it skips copying the region's data from the source to the destination "
"device, and only updates its metadata."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:97
msgid ""
"If the destination device supports discards, then by default dm-clone will "
"pass down discard requests to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:101
msgid "Background Hydration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:103
msgid ""
"dm-clone copies continuously from the source to the destination device, "
"until all of the device has been copied."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:106
msgid ""
"Copying data from the source to the destination device uses bandwidth. The "
"user can set a throttle to prevent more than a certain amount of copying "
"occurring at any one time. Moreover, dm-clone takes into account user I/O "
"traffic going to the devices and pauses the background hydration when there "
"is I/O in-flight."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:111
msgid ""
"A message `hydration_threshold <#regions>` can be used to set the maximum "
"number of regions being copied, the default being 1 region."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:114
msgid ""
"dm-clone employs dm-kcopyd for copying portions of the source device to the "
"destination device. By default, we issue copy requests of size equal to the "
"region size. A message `hydration_batch_size <#regions>` can be used to tune "
"the size of these copy requests. Increasing the hydration batch size results "
"in dm-clone trying to batch together contiguous regions, so we copy the data "
"in batches of this many regions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:121
msgid ""
"When the hydration of the destination device finishes, a dm event will be "
"sent to user space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:125
msgid "Updating on-disk metadata"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:127
msgid ""
"On-disk metadata is committed every time a FLUSH or FUA bio is written. If "
"no such requests are made then commits will occur every second. This means "
"the dm-clone device behaves like a physical disk that has a volatile write "
"cache. If power is lost you may lose some recent writes. The metadata should "
"always be consistent in spite of any crash."
msgstr ""

