#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:267
msgid ""
"We redirect reads, to not-yet-hydrated regions, to the source device. If "
"reading the source device has high latency and the user repeatedly reads "
"from the same regions, this behaviour could degrade performance. We should "
"use these reads as hints to hydrate the relevant regions sooner. Currently, "
"we rely on the page cache to cache these regions, so we hopefully don't end "
"up reading them multiple times from the source device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:274
msgid ""
"Release in-core resources, i.e., the bitmaps tracking which regions are "
"hydrated, after the hydration has finished."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:277
msgid ""
"During background hydration, if we fail to read the source or write to the "
"destination device, we print an error message, but the hydration process "
"continues indefinitely, until it succeeds. We should stop the background "
"hydration after a number of failures and emit a dm event for user space to "
"notice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:284
msgid "Why not...?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:286
msgid "We explored the following alternatives before implementing dm-clone:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:288
msgid ""
"Use dm-cache with cache size equal to the source device and implement a new "
"cloning policy:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:291
msgid ""
"The resulting cache device is not a one-to-one mirror of the source device "
"and thus we cannot remove the cache device once cloning completes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:294
msgid ""
"dm-cache writes to the source device, which violates our requirement that "
"the source device must be treated as read-only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:297
msgid "Caching is semantically different from cloning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:299
msgid "Use dm-snapshot with a COW device equal to the source device:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:301
msgid ""
"dm-snapshot stores its metadata in the COW device, so the resulting device "
"is not a one-to-one mirror of the source device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:304
msgid "No background copying mechanism."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:306
msgid ""
"dm-snapshot needs to commit its metadata whenever a pending exception "
"completes, to ensure snapshot consistency. In the case of cloning, we don't "
"need to be so strict and can rely on committing metadata every time a FLUSH "
"or FUA bio is written, or periodically, like dm-thin and dm-cache do. This "
"improves the performance significantly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:312
msgid ""
"Use dm-mirror: The mirror target has a background copying/mirroring "
"mechanism, but it writes to all mirrors, thus violating our requirement that "
"the source device must be treated as read-only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:316
msgid ""
"Use dm-thin's external snapshot functionality. This approach is the most "
"promising among all alternatives, as the thinly-provisioned volume is a one-"
"to-one mirror of the source device and handles reads and writes to un-"
"provisioned/not-yet-cloned areas the same way as dm-clone does."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:321
msgid "Still:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:323
msgid ""
"There is no background copying mechanism, though one could be implemented."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:325
msgid ""
"Most importantly, we want to support arbitrary block devices as the "
"destination of the cloning process and not restrict ourselves to thinly-"
"provisioned volumes. Thin-provisioning has an inherent metadata overhead, "
"for maintaining the thin volume mappings, which significantly degrades "
"performance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-clone.rst:331
msgid ""
"Moreover, cloning a device shouldn't force the use of thin-provisioning. On "
"the other hand, if we wish to use thin provisioning, we can just use a thin "
"LV as dm-clone's destination device."
msgstr ""
